<br />
<h2>
Elaine Equi
</h2>

<h1>
Two poems
</h1>

<br />
</td></tr></table></div>

<div>
<table width="535" summary="page content begins">
<tr>
<td>


<h4>Wittgenstein&#8217;s Colors</h4>

<p class="poem">
Blond<br />
Tamarind<br />
Bacon<br />
Fog<br />
<br />
Burlap<br />
Winter
Grass<br />
Semi-dark<br />
<br />
Tarn<br />
Goose<br />
Nutmeg<br />
<br />
Brown
Light<br />
Hot Blue<br />
<br />
Lion&#8217;s
Mane<br />
Liverspot<br />
Birch<br />
<img height="1" width="453"
src="equipoems00.png" 	alt="equipoems00.png" border="0" 
/><br />
<br />
<br />
</p>


<h4>Furniture Fantasy</h4>

<p class="poem">
Homeless club kids<br />
living
on rice, beans<br />
and Gitanes.<br />
<br />
All day he forces them<br />
to
strip<br />
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
              paint,<br />
<br />
sand hutches<br />
and
stain armoires<br />
to the music of Billie Holiday.<br />
<br />
Outdoors, under a
tarp<br />
even in rain.<br />
All this they gladly do<br />
without
complaint<br />
<br />
for how else<br />
will the owner<br />
know whose
love<br />
of antiques is true<br />
<br />
and who&#8217;s a fake
&#8212;<br />
<br />
which urchin<br />
to take<br />
to his ancient<br />
mahogany
sleigh bed<br />
<br />
and which to make<br />
curl up in<br />
the Morris
chair.<br />
<br />
<br />

</p></td></tr></table></div>

<div><table width="535" summary="^page content continues"><tr><td>
